# Changelog - xcesp-on-rtr

## 0.0.2

- Complete schema redesign: hierarchical `router > vrf > {interface, vlan,
  static-route}` with `address` child nodes for multi-address support
- `_types.schema`: custom types ‚Äî vlan-id, ip4-prefix, ip4-host, metric-val,
  table-id
- Replaced flat stubs: `vrf.schema`, `interface.schema`, `route.schema` ‚Üí
  full definitions + new `router.schema`, `vlan.schema`, `static-route.schema`,
  `address.schema`
- Config-to-objects rules: `router.py`, `vrf.py`, `interface.py`, `vlan.py`,
  `static-route.py` ‚Äî full implementations producing RtrXxx object INI sections
- Status-to-global rules: all five node types emit `oper-status`; interface and
  vlan also emit `link-state`
- `IpCmd` helper class: thin wrapper for iproute2 `ip` commands via
  `popen()`/`system()`; `parseOperstate()` for JSON link output
- `RtrCommon.h`: shared `RtrOperStatus` enum, `parseNsVrf()`, `splitCsv()`,
  `operStatusStr()`
- Five ProcObjects (all follow IDLE‚ÜíACTIVE pattern, monitor every 5 ticks):
  - `RtrRouterPObj`: Linux network namespace create/monitor
  - `RtrVrfPObj`: Linux VRF device create/monitor; auto-assigns routing table
    from VRF name hash if `TABLE` not specified
  - `RtrInterfacePObj`: physical device config ‚Äî namespace move, VRF binding,
    IP addresses, link state; LOS/MAJOR alarm on link-down when not shutdown
  - `RtrVlanPObj`: 802.1Q subinterface create/config; same LOS alarm logic
  - `RtrStaticRoutePObj`: static IPv4 route add/remove; re-adds if externally
    removed; VRF_TABLE key for VRF-aware routing
- `OnRtrRegister.cpp`: registers all 5 types via REGISTER_PROC_OBJECT
- `makefile`: added `src/objects/` compilation; fixed XCESPPROC path to
  `../xcespproc`; added `-I $(SRCDIR) -I $(SRCDIR)/objects` include paths

## 0.0.1

- Initial skeleton: project structure, schema stubs (interface/route/vrf),
  empty rule scripts, makefile, and registration stub (no ProcObjects yet)
